Body: Description: Previously, we had a 128 GB SSD in Azure, which has now been upgraded to 512 GB. However, the additional space has not been automatically allocated in the endpoint protector portal.
Invitation updated. Attendees: Andre Le Roux

Next Steps Updated: 2025.04.15:
We have a remote session scheduled for 2025.04.16. In our remote session we will extend the EPP appliance root partition via SSH in the backend.

What We've Learned Updated: 2025.04.16: The customer extended the Hard Disk size from 128 GB to 512 GB in Azure, a backend procedure was needed in order to extend the root partition for the EPP appliance.
